releases.name: v2.5.0
releases.body: Safety Histogram v2.5.0 features group stratification, as demonstrated [here](https://rhoinc.github.io/CAT/?re=c2FmZXR5LWhpc3RvZ3JhbQ==&ve=djIuNS4w&de=Y2xpbmljYWwtdHJpYWxzL3JlbmRlcmVyLXNwZWNpZmljL2FkYmRzLmNzdg==&&draw&controls=min).  This release also features annotated statistical tests, one that tests the normality of the distribution and a second that compares the distribution of each stratified set of results with that of the entire set of results.  View a full list of resolved issues [here](https://github.com/RhoInc/safety-histogram/issues?utf8=%E2%9C%93&q=is%3Aissue+milestone%3A2.5.0+).

releases.name: v2.4.1
releases.body: Fixes test-page and resolve minor bug regarding async table styling.

releases.name: v2.4.0
releases.body: Safety Histogram v2.4.0 adds user control of the binning algorithm and number of bins.  Additionally a new toggle controls whether the x-axis ticks appear between bins or evenly spaced along the axis.  View a full list of resolved issues [here](https://github.com/RhoInc/safety-histogram/issues?utf8=%E2%9C%93&q=is%3Aissue+milestone%3Av2.4.0+).

releases.name: v2.3.1
releases.body: Safety Histogram v2.3.1 updates the binning of results by using the range of the current x-domain rather than the range of the values.  This approach allows a more straightforward comparison of the full set of results and a subset of results because the bins remain the same.

releases.name: v2.3.0
releases.body: Safety Histogram v2.3.0 improves data cleaning, adds a binning algorithm, and simplifies clicking on really, really tiny little bars by allowing clicking anywhere in or above each bar.  View a full list of resolved issues [here](https://github.com/RhoInc/safety-histogram/issues?utf8=%E2%9C%93&q=is%3Aissue+milestone%3Av2.3.0+).

releases.name: v2.2.3
releases.body: Safety Histogram v2.2.3 improves handling of settings passed as strings instead of as arrays.

releases.name: v2.2.2
releases.body: Technical update adding `npm audit fix` to the build process and updating dependencies accordingly.

releases.name: v2.2.1
releases.body: Technical updates including updating dependencies and tweaks to test page and documentation.

releases.name: v2.2.0
releases.body: Safety Histogram v2.2.0 improves the data cleaning method and adds an algorithm that determines the precision of each measure.  View the full list of resolved issues [here](https://github.com/RhoInc/safety-histogram/issues?utf8=%E2%9C%93&q=is%3Aissue+milestone%3Av2.2.0+).

releases.name: v2.1.1
releases.body: safety-histogram v2.1.1 updates the control label of custom controls from _control-label_ to _wc-control-label_ to avoid css conflicts with bootstrap.

releases.name: v2.1.0
releases.body: Added new controls for interactive customization of the x-axis #59

releases.name: v2.0.4
releases.body:
Documentation update only. No code changes made.

![3](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/31038805/34171993-72f04f0c-e4be-11e7-82b1-cb6d165eeb60.PNG)

releases.name: v2.0.1
releases.body: Minor update so that filters with 0 or 1 levels no longer render. (#45)

releases.name: v2.0.0
releases.body: Version 2.0.0 of the Safety Histogram represents a major refactor, and includes many bug fixes and performance improvements. The overall framework using [webcharts-boilerplate](https://github.com/RhoInc/webcharts-wrapper-boilerplate) is still in place, but the secondary build creating a react framework has been removed, and several [configuration options](https://github.com/RhoInc/safety-histogram/wiki/Configuration) have been simplified, breaking backwards compatibility. A full list of resolved issues is available [here](https://github.com/RhoInc/safety-histogram/milestone/1?closed=1).
This release includes additional refactoring of the ChartFoundry renderer as described in the [webcharts templates boilerplate](https://github.com/RhoInc/webcharts-wrapper-boilerplate) library.

The framework of the library has been significantly revised (see the webcharts-wrapper-boilerplate library for framework details), but basic functionality remains the same.

This update also includes full documentation in the wiki.
This is the initial release of the Test Results Histogram. This interactive tool features a histogram that allows users to examine all of the data for a given lab or vital sign.

issues.title: Text parsing for p-values
issues.body:
0.00 -> <0.01
1.00 -> >0.99

# [Test notes](https://rhoinc.github.io/CAT/?re=c2FmZXR5LWhpc3RvZ3JhbQ==&ve=Z3JvdXAtY29tcGFyaXNvbnM=&de=Y2xpbmljYWwtdHJpYWxzL3JlbmRlcmVyLXNwZWNpZmljL2FkYmRzLmNzdg==&&draw&controls=min)
* Select _Aminotransferase, alanine (ALT) (pkat/L)_ from the _Measure_ dropdown.
* Verify in the main chart the p-value is formatted with a less than sign.
* Verify in the _Treatment B_ grouped histogram the p-value is formatted with a greater than sign.

issues.title: Add "validation" disclaimer to p-values
issues.body:
Add a note in the p-values mouseover with a link to the library used and a "this is not validated" disclaimer.

# [Test notes](https://rhoinc.github.io/CAT/?re=c2FmZXR5LWhpc3RvZ3JhbQ==&ve=Z3JvdXAtY29tcGFyaXNvbnM=&de=Y2xpbmljYWwtdHJpYWxzL3JlbmRlcmVyLXNwZWNpZmljL2FkYmRzLmNzdg==&&draw&controls=min)
* Verify a disclaimer appears in the tooltip of the info icons of the annotated p-values in both the main chart and the grouped histograms with this text: _Caution: This graphic has been thoroughly tested, but is not validated._.

issues.title: Update R test framework
issues.body: Very simple validation comparison program in /test, but would be good to update using `testthat` and then automatically run the test in the build process and in travisCI

issues.title: Multiple highlighted bars
issues.body:
1) First click a bar in the main chart
2) Then click a bar in the sub-chart
3) Now two bars are highlighted (see below). Boo!

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3680095/70242342-aca30f00-173e-11ea-9ed4-09e1656d8104.png)

# [Test notes](https://rhoinc.github.io/CAT/?re=c2FmZXR5LWhpc3RvZ3JhbQ==&ve=Z3JvdXAtY29tcGFyaXNvbnM=&de=Y2xpbmljYWwtdHJpYWxzL3JlbmRlcmVyLXNwZWNpZmljL2FkYmRzLmNzdg==&&draw&controls=min)
* Select an option from _Group by_ dropdown.
* Click bars in the grouped charts and in the main chart and try to get two bars highlighted.
* If you can't do it, it's okay, the test passes ;-)

pagination bug in latest version of webcharts
issues.body:
In test webcharts version 1.9.0-RC3, I noticed a pagination bug, where you can click on a bar in the chart with lots of records, page through the table for several pages, and then if you click on a bar with fewer records, it seems to retain the pagination, even if the new table does not have that many pages, so you end up with an empty table. It shows the correct number of records, and you can click a page or arrow button to be taken to a page with records on it, but the table should be properly refreshed when you click on a new bar.

Steps to recreate:
1. render the chart
2. click on one of the taller bars in the chart
3. paginate through the table to at least page 5 or 6
4. click on a much smaller bar in the chart


![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/17090469/31505377-c4690b82-af42-11e7-9598-d5e0b9705fe9.png)
